The character type called Tsundere refers to a person who initially seems cold but becomes friendly later on when they have known someone for some time. They are also said to be shy around strangers because it takes them time to open up about themselves.
Tsunderes tend to hide their feelings by giving others short remarks like "You're so stupid" (違うなよ), which may sound harsh at first, but really means nothing bad. In reality though, they can sometimes show a bit more than just an insult if provoked enough, especially towards those whom they trust deeply. Their behaviour towards other people often changes based on how they feel toward one another.

\begin{blockquote}
Atsuko Sakaki from \em{[Sakura Trick](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sakura_Trice)}
\end{blockquote}

<a href="https://i.stack.imgur.com/kJGcNm.png"><IMAGE></a>

\strong{\em{"Darling~, I’ll always love you! I will always keep loving you forever."}}

The Tsundere personality can be defined as "cold towards those who she likes" whereas the Kuudere means "a cold exterior but warm interior." Yanderes have a tough outer shell which they hide behind when it suits them; these people tend to be very strong-willed with an extremely high level of confidence. They often do what they want without regard for anyone else’s feelings, even going so far as to disregard their own safety. The last category would refer to the Dandare character type. It has been described as “the opposite side of the coin from the Tsundere.” This kind of person tends to act sweetly toward others until they show some sign of weakness, such as anger or fear, whereupon this same person becomes rude. In other words, he will treat someone nicely if they behave properly, yet if they misbehave, he may lash out verbally.
\end{blockquote}

