\begin{itemize}
\item As soon as the user types anything into the textbox, the `if` statement runs and checks if there has been activity for more than 5 seconds. In such case, the `if` statement ends before sending back a message to the server. This makes sure the system doesn't freeze when the keyboard isn't used for longer than five seconds. However, because the `else-branch` gets skipped here, it only works once every five seconds - making the timer always run from scratch again until another keypress occurs.

This results in a bug where the app stops working correctly during prolonged typing sessions.
\end{itemize}

